# ✅ 3. LINEAR REGRESSION (User Defined - Simplified)

```python
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.random.rand(100)
y = 4 + 3*x + np.random.randn(100)

# Formula
b1 = np.sum((x-x.mean())*(y-y.mean())) / np.sum((x-x.mean())**2)
b0 = y.mean() - b1*x.mean()

y_pred = b0 + b1*x

plt.scatter(x,y)
plt.plot(x,y_pred)
plt.title("Regression Line")
plt.show()

print("Slope:", b1)
print("Intercept:", b0)
```

